\f2\lang1049\'d1\f1\lang1033 onclusion : \line We utilized Kramer's method to discover the solutions to the system of equations. This technique is employed for solving systems of linear algebraic equations where the number of equations matches the number of unknowns, and the determinant of the coefficient matrix is non-zero. Through this laboratory exercise, I confirmed its efficacy.\par
